messages.content: You are an AI assistant that helps people find information. You will receive a task and think step by step. Then provide your final outcome following the regular expression 'Answer: ([A-Za-z ]+,\s*)*[A-Za-z ]+'

Pete’s Coffee, Carter Children, Nike, Sephora, and Bath and Body Works are connected to each other. Chickflea, Baskins and Robins, Levis, GNC Live Well, and Nike are all connected to each other. Marshalls, Paris Baguette, H&M, Zara, and Target are connected to each other. Carter Children, Nike, Sephora, and Bath and Body Works are connected to each other. Baskins and Robins, Levis, GNC Live Well, and Target are connected to each other. Paris Baguette, H&M, and Zara are connected to each other. Nike is connected to Bath and Body Works. Levis, GNC Live Well and Target are connected to each other. H&M is connected to Zara. Sephora is connected to Bath and Body Works. GNC Live Well is connected to Target. Assume now that Starbucks and Chickflea are connected. From Starbucks what is the path that yields the most reward? Please list the store names in order, separated by commas.

Step 1: Identify the groups of connected stores.
Group 1: Starbucks, Paris Baguette, H&M, Zara, Sephora
Group 2: Pete's Coffee, Carter Children, Nike, Sephora, Bath and Body Works

Group 5: Carter Children, Nike, Sephora, Bath and Body Works

Group 8: Nike, Bath and Body Works

Group 10: H&M, Zara
Group 11: Sephora, Bath and Body Works
Group 12: GNC Live Well, Target

Step 2: Determine the starting point (Starbucks) and the connection (Chickflea).
Starting point: Starbucks (Group 1)
Connection: Chickflea (Group 3)

Step 3: Identify the path from Starbucks to Chickflea.
Path: Starbucks (Group 1) -> Paris Baguette (Group 1 & 4) -> H&M (Group 1, 4, & 7) -> Zara (Group 1, 4, 7, & 10) -> Sephora (Group 1, 2, 5, & 11) -> Nike (Group 2, 3, 5, & 8) -> Chickflea (Group 3)

Step 4: List the store names in order.
Answer: Starbucks, Paris Baguette, H&M, Zara, Sephora, Nike, Chickflea
